<h4>Identifying computers that are to be swapped</h4>
<ul>
  <li>
    Click on the <%= link_to "To be swapped", to_be_swapped_path %> link from the <%= link_to "Inventory", inventory_index_path %>.
    <ul>
      <li class="muted">This will return all of the items whose warranty will expire within the cutoff date for that year.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    At anytime when a Warranty End Date is displayed there is a series of color coding (and tooltips) provided to inform you of an items warranty status.
    <ul>
      <li><span class="warranty expired">Dates like this indicate an expired warranty.</span></li>
      <li><span class="warranty almost-expired">Dates like this indicate the warranty expires in the next 6 months.</span></li>
      <li><span class="warranty expires-within-year">Dates like this indicate the warranty expires in the next year.</span></li>
      <li><span class="warranty expires-next-year">Dates like this indicate the warranty expires in the next 1 - 2 years.</span></li>
      <li><span class="warranty not-expiring-soon">Dates like this indicate the warranty won't expire for more than 2 years.</span></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<h4>Selecting the swap model (anybody)</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Find the computer to be swapped in the <%= link_to "inventory", inventory_location_path %> and click on the heading.</li>
  <li>Click the 'Choose Swap Model' link in the sidebar.</li>
  <li>Select the model that you would like to swap the machine for.</li>
</ol>
<h4>Swapping the item in the inventory (EP)</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Find the computer to be swapped in the <%= link_to "inventory", inventory_location_path %> and click on the heading.</li>
  <li>
    Click the 'Create Swap Record' link in the sidebar.
    <ul>
      <li class="muted">If there is no "Create Swap Record" link in the sidebar that means the user has not selected their swap model.</li>
      <li class="muted">This will create a new item in the inventory that merges the data from the old and new machines into a record.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the "Swap" link in the Options sidebar of the old item in the inventory.
    <ul>
      <li class="muted">This will bring up a list of equipment that belongs to that user (excluding the old equipment).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the red "Swap" button next to the new item that will replace the current item.
    <ul>
      <li class="muted">This will remove the user of the old computer, but it will remain in the invenotry.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Add any remaining details about the new computer.</li>
</ol>